The paper deals with the construction of spanner graphs, which are commonly studied in the field of computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The application of spanners in network backbones suggests a possible fit in the sub-category of network science (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the emergence of good spanners in reality, which could be interpreted as a study of complex systems (cs.SI) or data mining (cs.DM).
